From: Ilya Leoshkevich <iii@linux.ibm.com>
Date: Mon, 12 May 2025 22:57:31 +0200
Subject: s390/bpf: Remove the orig_call NULL check
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
Git-commit: 8e57cf09c84cac99eb31354a3cc70f8b8981bfc2
References: jsc#PED-14653

Now that orig_call can never be NULL, remove the respective check.

Signed-off-by: Ilya Leoshkevich <iii@linux.ibm.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250512221911.61314-3-iii@linux.ibm.com
Signed-off-by: Alexei Starovoitov <ast@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Hoyeon Lee <hoyeon.lee@suse.com>
---
 arch/s390/net/bpf_jit_comp.c |    5 ++---
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/arch/s390/net/bpf_jit_comp.c
+++ b/arch/s390/net/bpf_jit_comp.c
@@ -2583,9 +2583,8 @@ static int __arch_prepare_bpf_trampoline
 	if (nr_stack_args > MAX_NR_STACK_ARGS)
 		return -ENOTSUPP;
 
-	/* Return to %r14, since func_addr and %r0 are not available. */
-	if ((!func_addr && !(flags & BPF_TRAMP_F_ORIG_STACK)) ||
-	    (flags & BPF_TRAMP_F_INDIRECT))
+	/* Return to %r14 in the struct_ops case. */
+	if (flags & BPF_TRAMP_F_INDIRECT)
 		flags |= BPF_TRAMP_F_SKIP_FRAME;
 
 	/*
